 {"id":"bd-3ro","title":"Implement on_duplicate handling behavior","description":"# Duplicate Handling (on_duplicate)

## Background
Python FastMCP provides on_duplicate setting to control behavior when registering a component with a name that already exists. Options:
- "error" - Raise an error (strictest)
- "warn" - Log warning, keep original
- "replace" - Replace with new component
- "ignore" - Silently keep original

## Requirements

### Configuration Enum
```rust
/// Behavior when registering duplicate component names
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, Default)]
pub enum DuplicateBehavior {
    /// Raise an error (fail registration)
    Error,
    /// Log warning, keep original component
    #[default]
    Warn,
    /// Replace original with new component
    Replace,
    /// Silently keep original
    Ignore,
}
```

### ServerBuilder Configuration
```rust
impl ServerBuilder {
    /// Set behavior when registering duplicate component names
    pub fn on_duplicate(self, behavior: DuplicateBehavior) -> Self
}
```

### Router Integration
Apply on_duplicate behavior in:
- router.add_tool()
- router.add_resource()
- router.add_prompt()

```rust
fn register_component(&mut self, name: &str, component: T, behavior: DuplicateBehavior) -> Result<(), McpError> {
    if self.components.contains_key(name) {
        match behavior {
            DuplicateBehavior::Error => return Err(McpError::duplicate(name)),
            DuplicateBehavior::Warn => {
                log::warn!("Duplicate component '{}', keeping original", name);
                return Ok(());
            }
            DuplicateBehavior::Replace => {
                log::debug!("Replacing component '{}'", name);
            }
            DuplicateBehavior::Ignore => return Ok(()),
        }
    }
    self.components.insert(name.to_owned(), component);
    Ok(())
}
```

